The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, August 10, 2004 				 Man on fast dies
																								Dehra Dun, Aug. 9 (PTI): Baba Mohan Uttarakhandi, who was on indefinite fast since July 2 demanding that Gairsen be made the permanent capital of Uttaranchal, died today following severe chest pain. Chief minister N.D. Tiwari has ordered an inquiry into the death of the 60-year-old baba, who had refused to end his fast-unto-death despite several appeals from political leaders and social organisations.																								Tiwari today recalled his valuable contribution to the Uttarakhand statehood movement and ordered the commissioner of Garhwal to submit a report on the cause of his death within a week.																								The baba, en ex-serviceman, died early this morning at a hospital in Karnprayag in Chamoli district. He had been on indefinite fast in Bainital and was forcibly evicted after his condition deteriorated.																								A post-mortem is being conducted to ascertain the cause of death, officials said. The chief minister has asked the Chamoli MLA, Anusuya Prasad Maikhuri, to represent him during the cremation, which will be held with full state honours, an official release said. 																								Tiwari has sanctioned a financial assistance of Rs 5 lakh for the babas family.																								The vice-chairman of the Rajya Nirman Andolankari Kalyan Parishad, Dhirendra, demanded that the Virendra Dixit Commission, set up to decide the states permanent capital, submit its report at the earliest.
